TY  - JOUR
TI  - Simple Finite Horizon Bubbles Robust to Higher Order Knowledge
AU  - Conlon, John R.
AB  - [An asymmetric information model of a finite horizon "nth order" rational asset price bubble is presented, where <tex-math>$(\text{all agents know that})^{n}$</tex-math> the asset is worthless. Also, the model has only two agents, so the first order version of the bubble is simpler than other first order bubbles in the literature.]
