TY  - JOUR
TI  - The Error in Rejection Probability of Simple Autocorrelation Robust Tests
AU  - Jansson, Michael
AB  - [A new class of autocorrelation robust test statistics is introduced. The class of tests generalizes the Kiefer, Vogelsang, and Bunzel (2000) test in a manner analogous to Anderson and Darling's (1952) generalization of the Cramér-von Mises goodness of fit test. In a Gaussian location model, the error in rejection probability of the new tests is found to be <tex-math>$O(T^{-1}\ \text{log}\ T)$</tex-math>, where T denotes the sample size.]
